{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_noone_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280600246/1930010801/0079.xml":{"full_text":"A-12\nWIN STRUGGLE\nTO CONTROL FIRM\n\nMotion Picture Magnate Now\nin Midst es Fight Over\nVast interests.\nBY JOHN r. SINCLAIR.\nSpecial Dispatch to The Star.\nNEW YORK, January B.\u2014Sherwood\nEddy, American business man and\nworld traveler, writing from India on\noondltlona there, aaya, \"I believe the\nI situation is far more serious than is\nrealised in Great Britain or America.\u201d\nGreat Britain, after having invested\n$5,000,000,000 in India\u2019s industries, built\n40.000 miles of railroads, irrigated\n25.000.000 acres of lands and established\na national system of education, finds\nIndia's two great leaders. Mahatma\n...Gandhi and Jawahar lal Nehru, opposed\nto further British extension of power in\nthat vast continent of 500.000.000\npeople.\nWhile Mr. .Eddy was not permitted to\ni quote these leaders directly, he says that\nIndia's millions will follow either Gan\ndhi or Nehru to the end. Nehru \u2014rich,\nyoung, daring, educated in the English\nuniversities \u2014holds opinions similar to\nthose held by Thomas Jefferson.\nWt belongs to the left wing of the\nmdian movement, which stands for\ncomplete independence, with or without\nviolence.\nGandhi, older, more experienced, more\nconservative, belongs to the right wing,\nand Is willing to accept dominion status,\nwithin the empire.\nIndia\u2019s leaden object to the British\narmy expenses .ot $200,000,000 a year,\nwhen the average per capita income is\nonly $27.75 a year, or less than cents\na day. Even today. #2 per cent of the\npeople of India cannot read nor write.\nBut. above all. according to Mr. Eddy.\nIndians resent the so-called Anglo-\nSaxon superiority complex. Says Gan\ndhi: \u201cI believe there is no real freedom\nfor India under the British connection\nif Englishmen cannot give tip the fetish\nof their predestined superiority. We\nhave co-operated long enough in our\nown degradtkm.\u201d Britain has many\npreblems to solve. What to do with\nIndia is probably the most Important.\nWilliam Box. veteran of many a bit\nter business struggle\u2014restless, reticent,\nsharing his secrets with few\u2014is using\nall his resourcefulness in his latest\nstruggle to maintain personal control of\nhis vast motion picture enterprises.\nWhen J. E. Otterson of the Western\nElectric affiliations and Harry Stuart\nof Halsey Stuart A Co. were appointed\nwith William fox as a trustees com\nmittee to examine into affairs, it was\nthought the matter would iron itself\nout quickly.\nBut not so. Mr. Fox. owning a\nmajority interest in the no par class\nB voting stock, is understood to be un\nwilling to turn over control under the\nconditions so far laid down.\nIt is no small matter in these days\nto borrow $145,000,000 to meet unse\ncured debts and immediate future com\nmitments. This is the problem which\nfacee Mr. Fox.\nThere have been many rumors. One\nreport was that A1 Smith, former\ngovernor of New York, and a friend of\nWilliam Fox. had become interested\nand was going to take charge. Another\nI\nColumbia Building Association\nPays 5% \u00a3SX=\u00a3\n20 Years' Successful Business Without the Loss of a Dime I\nH or More Will Start Tour Thrift Account\nSee U\u00ab When Yon Want a Real Estate Loan\n(Under Government Supervision)\n716 11th St. N.W.\n\u25a0M I msss\u00df\u00df\u00dfawiH ii \u00abi 1 \u25a0\u25a0'mn'fln\u00dfwriiiwi \"\"miai'ir 'irr\u2018rr\"r in sin itth rir-.-'Tim.\nOrganize Yout Office\nCTOW A DAVIS desks \u201di\nA methodically ar-\nranged to facilitate or* nfl\nW/\u00a3 derly business methods.\njff Lei Ofte\u00ab ekeiency end working |W|\nv Mr spaed is accelerated by these\npjy. modern conveniently arranged\nI[A\\ fra deaka\u2014impressing your custom-\nJial 1 /Ml era with their atately elegance. A\nwdV Stow A Davit deaka are riehly f\nSniahed. expressing character and\ndiatinction in many materiala\u2014 d\nmade in attractive styles, sires s.