rs\u2019 Association and the State banking\nassociations of Oregon. Washington,\nIdaho. Montana. Utah and Wyoming.\n10-CENT CARFARE DUE\n(P BALTIMORE SHORTLY\ngpaelal Diwateh to Tha Star.\nBALTIMORE, January g.\u2014A fiat 10-\ncent carefare will be In effect In Balti\nmore within 20 days, according to offi\ncials of the Public Service Commission.\nSteuart Purcell, a member of the\ncommission, declared he believes that\nthe new rate will go into effect within\na month, with only the briefest of\nformalities before the commission. He\nadded:\n\"We probably have sufficient data on\nhand now to figure out the new car\nrates without any elaborate hearings.\n\"The Supreme Court settled on the\nissue so far as we are concerned, and\nthere is nothing for uc to do but comply\nwith its ruling.\u201d\nJ. Frank Harper, another member of\nthe commission, said he thought a\nhearing would have to be held before\nFor Simplicity\nOUR Real Eatate Loan Plan xe\neaay to understand and oi\nvalue to you.\nConsult\nW E^VEJLBROC\nTT REALTORS O\n809 15th St. A.r. District 9486\nMortgage Loan Correspondent\nMetropolitan Life Insurance Company\nthe nesrnua can be determined. but\nhe declined to U7 how protracted he\nthought the hearing would be. He\nadded:\n\"We must cet new figures on Income\nand operation for the y*ar and a half\nthat has passed since the last hearings.\nHe said no hearing could be held\nuntil the remand comes from the Su\npreme Court giving official notice of\nthe derision.\n\nRAILROAD TRAFFIC.\nSt the Associated Press.\nChristmas week resulted in the usual\nsharp curtailment of railroad traffic,\nthe American Hallway Association noted\ntoday in making public its regular\nweekly compilation of total carloadings\nhandled. Figures for the week and\ncomparable periods follow: Week end\ning December 31. M 1 ,445 ears: preced\ning week. g42,4M cars; same week last\nyear, \u00a747,974 cars.\ni Alin\n3yi f j Jj.\nFIVF\n\\JOUR POI.NT\ns. S H\nTHE NEW\nKOOLMOTOR\nOIL\nThe Perfect 